                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in brown ink by a modern hand: <quote>94</quote>; centre page, in black ink: <quote>Autor Sacri huius Poematii est PETRVS de RIGA qui claruit pavlo post Annum Christi 1100 Barthius Adversar. Lib. 31. Cap. 15.</quote>; below in brown ink: <quote>Stephanii hand</quote>; bottom right corner: a read seal, motif not visible. According to a former librarian's note this is the seal of Magnus Gabriel de la Gardie.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="Leaf_1r" to="Leaf_1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Centre page, in brown ink by a 19th century hand: <quote>Petrus de Riga, Auora. Poema Sacrum</quote>; bottom of page by the same hand: <quote>Har tillhört Stephanus Stephanius och efter honom Magnus Gabriel de la Gardie</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="SL1r" to="SL1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>In brow ink by a modern hand: 26 lines of text in Latin concerning the author and the present work.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="SL2v" to="SL2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top of page in brown ink by a modern hand: a copy of the rubric and the first 10 lines of the Aurora.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false">
                                <p>Early modern binding. Parchment over cardboard. 2 pairs of leather straps. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in ink: <quote>Petrus de Riga N<hi rend="super">o</hi> 21</quote>; in ink: <quote>96</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 169</quote>. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, upper part of cover in pencil (faded): <quote>Uppbyggelselitt</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
